Question - 08: What is the Difference between HTTP and HTTPS?
Answer:
ğŸ” Difference Between HTTP and HTTPS
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
      Feature	  |              HTTP	            |                HTTPS                     |
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ğŸ”’ Full Form	  |    HyperText Transfer Protocol	|   HyperText Transfer Protocol Secure     |
ğŸ” Security	      |           âŒ Not secure	        |        âœ… Encrypted using SSL/TLS        |
ğŸŒ URL Format	  |         http://example.com	    |            https://example.com           |
ğŸ§‘â€ğŸ’» Data Safety	  |     Data is sent as plain text	|   Data is encrypted( safe from hackers)  |
ğŸ“¶ Used For	      |      Basic websites or testing	|   Secure sites (banking, login pages)    |
ğŸ” Lock Icon	  |         âŒ No lock in browser	|         âœ… Lock ğŸ”’ shown in browser      |
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§  Simple Explanation:
    - HTTP: Just sends and receives data â€” but anyone can see it if they intercept it.
    - HTTPS: Adds a security layer (SSL/TLS) so your data is private and protected.

ğŸ“Œ Summary:
    - HTTPS = HTTP + Security
    - Use HTTPS when you care about privacy, security, and trust â€” which is almost always!

